WEBVTT

00:03.100 --> 00:04.333
PREVIOUSLY ON
"SINGLE LADIES"...

00:04.333 --> 00:05.800
I HEARD YOU SAY THAT
AARON WAS YOUR PROFESSOR?

00:05.800 --> 00:06.967
IT'S JUST SEX.

00:06.967 --> 00:08.267
HE SEEMS WAY MORE
INTO YOU.

00:08.267 --> 00:10.333
YOU'RE ENDING IT?
DID IT EVER REALLY BEGIN?

00:10.333 --> 00:11.533
April: I HAVE A LITTLE MONEY

00:11.533 --> 00:12.800
THAT I AM WILLING
TO INVEST IN YOU.

00:12.800 --> 00:14.967
HE ISN'T HERE?
REED, WHERE THE HELL ARE YOU?

00:14.967 --> 00:17.133
Ma'am, this isn't Reed.

00:17.133 --> 00:18.800
MR. DURHAM OVERDOSED.

00:18.800 --> 00:21.200
YOU'RE SLEEPING ON MY COUCH
UNTIL WE FINISH THIS ALBUM,

00:21.200 --> 00:22.433
SO GET COMFORTABLE.

00:22.433 --> 00:23.600
ARE YOU SAYING YOU WERE
NEVER IN LOVE WITH ME?!

00:23.600 --> 00:24.733
IF YOU HADN'T PRESSED ME,

00:24.733 --> 00:26.767
I WOULDN'T HAVE REALIZED
I WAS SETTLING WITH YOU.

00:26.767 --> 00:29.400
THANK YOU FOR BEING
A COMPLETE GENTLEMAN.

00:29.400 --> 00:31.567
IT'S RARE FOR ME
TO MEET A WOMAN THESE DAYS

00:31.567 --> 00:33.433
WHO WANTS TO TAKE THE TIME
TO GET TO KNOW A MAN.

00:33.433 --> 00:35.100
Valerie: I TAKE IT
WOODY'S COMING OVER TONIGHT?

00:35.100 --> 00:36.300
I'M GOING TO MALCOLM'S.

00:36.300 --> 00:38.500
MALCOLM, PLEASE DON'T
PLAY WITH MY HEART,

00:38.500 --> 00:39.967
BECAUSE IT'S REALLY IN THIS.

00:39.967 --> 00:42.333
MINE IS, TOO.

00:42.333 --> 00:45.000
* SINGLE *
YEAH, YEAH.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.733
CAN YOU SAY LOVE CITY?

00:46.733 --> 00:48.933
* LADIES *

00:48.933 --> 00:50.600
CRAZY, CRAZY.

00:50.600 --> 00:52.633
* WHAT I WANT IS UP TO ME *

00:52.633 --> 00:54.633
* I CAN FOLLOW, I CAN LEAD *

00:54.633 --> 01:00.333
* LOSE CONTROL *

01:00.333 --> 01:02.067
* YOU CAN'T GET MY LOVE *

01:02.067 --> 01:05.633
* I KNOW YOU WANT IT *
* OH, YEAH *

01:05.633 --> 01:07.633
* YOU WANT IT *

01:07.633 --> 01:10.167
* SINGLE LADIES *

01:10.167 --> 01:12.300
WHERE MY SINGLE LADIES AT?

01:47.667 --> 01:49.300
[ SCOFFS ]

01:49.300 --> 01:51.267
CRAB CAKES
AND EGGS BENEDICT?

01:51.267 --> 01:53.200
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LOVE YOUR CHEF,

01:53.200 --> 01:55.567
BUT I SWEAR
HE'S TRYING TO MAKE ME FAT.

01:55.567 --> 01:59.067
[ CHUCKLES ] YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT, BABE.

01:59.067 --> 02:01.367
BUT, UH, IF IT MAKES YOU
FEEL BETTER,

02:01.367 --> 02:04.067
I PROMISE I'LL HELP YOU
BURN OFF MORE CALORIES LATER.

02:04.067 --> 02:05.367
[ LAUGHS ]

02:05.367 --> 02:09.433
I'VE BEEN HERE SO LONG, I'VE RUN
OUT OF CLOTHES...AGAIN.

02:09.433 --> 02:11.633
I NEED TO GO HOME.

02:11.633 --> 02:13.700
I'LL BUY YOU MORE CLOTHES.
[ MUG CLATTERS ]

02:13.700 --> 02:15.200
I'LL TAKE YOU UP
ON THE OFFER,

02:15.200 --> 02:17.067
BUT I STILL HAVE
TO GO HOME.

02:17.067 --> 02:19.867
I KEEP CANCELING PLANS
WITH VAL AND APRIL.

02:19.867 --> 02:22.867
I'M ONE EXCUSE AWAY
FROM LOSING TWO FRIENDS.

02:22.867 --> 02:25.067
I HAVEN'T CALLED THE OFFICE
OR MY POPS IN DAYS.

02:25.067 --> 02:26.833
I GUESS WE, UH, HAVE BEEN
SHUTTING THE WORLD OUT

02:26.833 --> 02:29.800
EVER SINCE WE MADE IT
OFFICIAL.

02:29.800 --> 02:32.300
HOW ABOUT
I'LL CALL MY PEOPLE OVER,

02:32.300 --> 02:33.967
YOU CALL YOUR PEOPLE OVER,

02:33.967 --> 02:36.267
AND I'LL COOK BRUNCH
FOR EVERYONE?

02:36.267 --> 02:39.300
THAT WAY, WE CAN SEE THEM
AND STILL BE TOGETHER.

02:39.300 --> 02:40.733
WE GOT IT BAD, HUH?

02:40.733 --> 02:42.333
OH, YEAH, WE SPRUNG.

02:42.333 --> 02:43.733
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

02:43.733 --> 02:46.833
[ SIGHS ] NOW ABOUT
YOU COOKING BRUNCH...

02:46.833 --> 02:48.200
MM-HMM.

02:48.200 --> 02:49.867
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANNA
TRY THAT, BABE?

02:49.867 --> 02:52.367
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I CAN COOK BREAKFAST.

02:52.367 --> 02:55.967
IT'S THE AFTER-5:00 FOODS
I'M NOT SO SURE ABOUT.

02:55.967 --> 02:58.633
FINE. WHATEVER YOU WANT.

02:58.633 --> 03:00.700
THAT'S A DANGEROUS THING
TO SAY TO A WOMAN

03:00.700 --> 03:04.367
WITH A PRADA OBSESSION.

03:04.367 --> 03:05.967
HMM.
MM-HMM.

03:05.967 --> 03:07.900
* EYES CLOSING *

03:07.900 --> 03:11.133
* LIPS SLOWLY SAYING YES *

03:11.133 --> 03:13.633
* EYES CLOSING *

03:13.633 --> 03:15.267
* EYES CLOSING *

03:15.267 --> 03:18.233
* LIPS SLOWLY SAYING YES *

03:18.233 --> 03:19.767
* EYES CLO-- *

03:19.767 --> 03:22.867
HEY, YOU. I'M GLAD TO SEE
YOU'RE HARD AT WORK.

03:22.867 --> 03:25.967
YEAH, I'VE BEEN IN A GROOVE.
IT'S BEEN PRETTY INTENSE,

03:25.967 --> 03:27.533
BUT I THINK
WHAT I GOT'S WORKIN'.

03:27.533 --> 03:30.700
I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR IT.
WAIT.

03:30.700 --> 03:32.367
WHAT DID YOU DO WITH THE BOXES
THAT WERE RIGHT THERE?

03:32.367 --> 03:33.533
OH, I'M TRYING TO BE
A GOOD ROOMMATE.

03:33.533 --> 03:34.833
I PUT SOME THINGS AWAY.

03:34.833 --> 03:36.467
YOU DIDN'T UNPACK
MY BEDROOM STUFF, DID YOU?

03:36.467 --> 03:39.167
OH, NO, I HAVE FIVE SISTERS.
I WAS TRAINED WELL.

03:39.167 --> 03:41.367
I STUCK TO THE BOXES
MARKED "KITCHEN."

03:41.367 --> 03:43.067
THAT'S SWEET.

03:43.067 --> 03:44.700
DID YOU WORK YOUR MAGIC
IN THE BATHROOM, TOO?

03:44.700 --> 03:46.367
UH, I WAS JUST ABOUT TO,

03:46.367 --> 03:47.833
BUT THEN I HEARD
THIS HOOK IN MY HEAD,

03:47.833 --> 03:49.567
AND I HAD TO LAY IT DOWN.
LISTEN.

03:49.567 --> 03:50.967
[ BUTTON CLICKS ]

03:50.967 --> 03:52.233
***

03:52.233 --> 03:53.967
* DRIVING FAST *

03:53.967 --> 03:56.267
* THROW YOUR RIGHT FOOT *

03:56.267 --> 03:57.467
* ON THE GAS *

03:57.467 --> 03:59.467
* HAIR BLOWING *

03:59.467 --> 04:01.067
* ARMS POSING *

04:01.067 --> 04:05.367
* LIPS SLOWLY SAYING "YES" *

04:05.367 --> 04:07.667
[ BUTTON CLICKS, MUSIC STOPS ]
WHATCHU THINK?

04:07.667 --> 04:10.800
I THINK...
IT'S A GOOD START.

04:10.800 --> 04:12.833
YOU THINK IT SUCKS?
I WOULDN'T GO THAT FAR.

04:12.833 --> 04:14.467
[ SIGHS ] BUT YOU DON'T LIKE IT.
IT'S NOT THAT I DON'T LIKE IT.

04:14.467 --> 04:16.867
IT'S JUST...
IT'S THE KIND OF SONG

04:16.867 --> 04:18.333
THAT YOU GET STUCK
IN YOUR HEAD

04:18.333 --> 04:20.067
BECAUSE YOU'VE HEARD IT ON
THE RADIO OVER AND OVER AGAIN,

04:20.067 --> 04:22.067
BUT YOU NEVER BUY IT,
AND THEN IN SIX MONTHS,

04:22.067 --> 04:23.367
YOU FORGET IT.

04:23.367 --> 04:24.933
YOU JUST DESCRIBED, LIKE,
HALF THE SONGS

04:24.933 --> 04:26.100
ON THE "BILLBOARD" HOT 100,

04:26.100 --> 04:27.867
AND THEY'RE "FORGETTABLE"
ALL THE WAY TO THE BANK.

04:27.867 --> 04:29.967
IRONICALLY, THE SONGS OF YOURS
THAT I LIKE THE MOST

04:29.967 --> 04:31.667
WERE THE SONGS
THAT WES THREW OUT.

04:31.667 --> 04:33.767
THAT STUFF WAS MORE ORIGINAL.
I FELT YOU.

04:33.767 --> 04:35.467
YEAH, BUT WES DIDN'T FEEL ME,

04:35.467 --> 04:37.067
AND FACE IT,
THAT GUY KNOWS HITS.

04:37.067 --> 04:39.833
YEAH, BUT WES WAS MISSING
WHAT'S SPECIAL ABOUT YOU,

04:39.833 --> 04:42.067
AND IF YOU RELEASE
A CRAP BOY BAND SONG NOW,

04:42.067 --> 04:43.467
AND IT DOESN'T HIT,

04:43.467 --> 04:45.533
YOU'RE NOT GONNA GET THE KIND
OF RESPECT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR,

04:45.533 --> 04:46.833
AND YOU'RE GONNA BE
COMPLETELY OFF THE MAP.

04:46.833 --> 04:48.233
I DON'T THINK
IT'S NECESSARILY WRONG

04:48.233 --> 04:50.333
TO DO A SONG LIKE THIS.

04:50.333 --> 04:53.300
BUT I'LL KEEP WORKING ON IT
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL BETTER.

04:53.300 --> 04:54.600
IT WOULD
MAKE ME FEEL BETTER.

04:54.600 --> 04:55.633
[ HORNS HONKING IN DISTANCE ]

04:55.633 --> 04:57.067
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:59.633 --> 05:01.500
IT WOULD ALSO MAKE ME FEEL
BETTER IF YOU, UH...

05:01.500 --> 05:03.200
[ SMACKS LIPS ]
PUT AWAY YOUR DIRTY LAUNDRY.

05:03.200 --> 05:05.333
I-I CAN'T...
[ MUSIC RESUMES PLAYING ]

05:05.333 --> 05:07.633
OR ARE YOU?
IT'S REED'S WORKING TIME.
IT'S WORKING TIME

05:07.633 --> 05:09.267
FOR ME RIGHT NOW.
OH, YEAH. OKAY.

05:14.900 --> 05:16.200
KEISH?

05:16.200 --> 05:18.533
I THINK BRUNCH
IS A FANTASTIC IDEA.

05:18.533 --> 05:19.733
MM-HMM.

05:19.733 --> 05:20.733
BUT...

05:20.733 --> 05:21.967
"BUT" WHAT?

05:21.967 --> 05:23.567
ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANNA TRY THAT?

05:23.567 --> 05:25.967
MAYBE YOU SHOULD HAVE IT
CATERED. I KNOW A GREAT PLACE.

05:25.967 --> 05:28.867
WHY IS EVERYONE ACTING LIKE
I'VE NEVER BEEN IN A KITCHEN?

05:28.867 --> 05:30.300
I CAN COOK!

05:30.300 --> 05:31.800
[ LAUGHS ]

05:31.800 --> 05:34.667
JUST BE THERE, PLEASE.
YOU KNOW I WILL BE.

05:34.667 --> 05:38.367
SO...WHERE ARE YOU
AND JERRY GOING TONIGHT?

05:38.367 --> 05:40.233
THE SOLOMON CLUB
FOR DINNER.

05:40.233 --> 05:42.267
OH, SO HE CONTINUES
TO IMPRESS.

05:42.267 --> 05:45.067
[ GIGGLES ] YES, HE DOES,
AND I NEED TO HURRY,

05:45.067 --> 05:48.433
BECAUSE HE SENT A CAR FOR ME,
AND IT'S WAITING DOWNSTAIRS.

05:48.433 --> 05:51.500
OKAY, MISS PRIVATE CLUB
WITH THE PERSONAL CHAUFFEUR.

05:51.500 --> 05:52.833
[ LAUGHS ]

05:52.833 --> 05:54.933
WASN'T IT YOU WHO SAID YOU
DIDN'T NEED A MAN WITH MONEY?

05:54.933 --> 05:57.667
[ SIGHS ]
MM-HMM. YOU SURE ARE
GETTING COMFORTABLE.

05:57.667 --> 05:59.267
CAN YOU JUST ZIP IT,
PLEASE?

05:59.267 --> 06:00.533
I'M TRYING.

06:00.533 --> 06:02.467
[ CLEARS THROAT ] I WAS
TALKING ABOUT YOUR LIPS.

06:02.467 --> 06:03.700
[ ZIPS DRESS ]

06:03.700 --> 06:04.933
OH! [ LAUGHS ]

06:04.933 --> 06:07.100
[ CELL PHONE BUZZES ]

06:07.100 --> 06:08.733
[ BUZZES ]
HUH.

06:08.733 --> 06:10.100
HELLO?

06:10.100 --> 06:13.233
WHO IS THIS?

06:13.233 --> 06:16.367
WHY ARE YOU CALLING ME?

06:16.367 --> 06:17.700
[ Whispers ] IT'S QUINN.

06:17.700 --> 06:20.133
QUINN? WHEN DID YOU GET
A FRIENDS...

06:20.133 --> 06:22.433
[ raises voice ]
FAMILY, AND LOSERS PLAN?

06:22.433 --> 06:25.067
NO, QUINN. I'M VERY BUSY.
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO TALK,

06:25.067 --> 06:27.433
AND I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT WE WOULD TALK ABOUT.

06:27.433 --> 06:28.433
I CAN THINK
OF A FEW THINGS.

06:28.433 --> 06:29.567
I DON'T MEAN TO BE RUDE,

06:29.567 --> 06:32.133
BUT I'M ON MY WAY SOMEWHERE,
SO I HAVE TO GO.

06:32.133 --> 06:33.533
MM-HMM.

06:39.300 --> 06:41.700
[ GASPS ] QUINN.

06:41.700 --> 06:43.733
AW, HELL, NAW.

06:43.733 --> 06:46.067
WHAT'S UP, VAL?
CAN I TALK TO YOU?

06:46.067 --> 06:48.067
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING
AT MY HOUSE?

06:48.067 --> 06:49.433
I'M SORRY FOR JUST
SHOWING UP,

06:49.433 --> 06:51.067
BUT I KNEW YOU WOULD
ALWAYS BE TOO BUSY

06:51.067 --> 06:52.533
TO TALK TO ME
ON THE PHONE, SO --

06:52.533 --> 06:53.733
SO YOU THOUGHT IT WAS
A GOOD IDEA

06:53.733 --> 06:54.967
TO FORCE ME TO TALK TO YOU?

06:54.967 --> 06:57.300
NO. BUT IT'S IMPORTANT.

06:57.300 --> 06:58.433
I WOULDN'T BE HERE
IF IT WASN'T.

06:58.433 --> 07:01.067
DON'T YOU HAVE ONE BAD KNEE
ALREADY?

07:01.067 --> 07:03.500
YOU NEED TO BACK UP
OUTTA HERE BEFORE YOU HAVE TWO.

07:03.500 --> 07:06.500
VAL, CAN I HAVE A MOMENT
WITH YOU ALONE, PLEASE?

07:06.500 --> 07:07.600
NO, YOU CAN'T.

07:07.600 --> 07:10.633
YOU HAVE FIVE YEARS
OF MOMENTS ALONE WITH VAL.

07:10.633 --> 07:12.133
YOU DIDN'T SAY
THE RIGHT THINGS THEN,

07:12.133 --> 07:14.500
AND I'M SURE YOU HAVE NOTHING
WORTH SAYING NOW.

07:14.500 --> 07:16.800
KEISHA,
I KNOW THIS IS YOUR GIRL,

07:16.800 --> 07:19.367
AND IT'S YOUR DUTY
TO BE ALL RILED UP.

07:19.367 --> 07:22.267
BUT ALL DUE RESPECT,
THIS IS BETWEEN ME AND VAL.

07:22.267 --> 07:24.267
OKAY?
SO YOU COULD YOU JUST --

07:24.267 --> 07:25.400
I COULD, BUT I WON'T.

07:25.400 --> 07:27.833
I BIT MY TONGUE
WHEN YOU BROKE MY GIRL'S HEART

07:27.833 --> 07:30.633
AND WALKED OUT ON HER
IN FRONT OF A ROOMFUL OF PEOPLE.

07:30.633 --> 07:33.067
I BIT MY TONGUE AGAIN
WHEN YOU GOT ENGAGED

07:33.067 --> 07:34.467
A FEW MONTHS LATER.

07:34.467 --> 07:37.700
SO I'LL BE DAMNED
IF I BITE MY --
KEISH.

07:37.700 --> 07:40.133
IT'S OKAY.

07:40.133 --> 07:41.367
I CAN HANDLE THIS.

07:41.367 --> 07:42.800
[ SIGHS ]

07:45.667 --> 07:46.900
I'M IN A HURRY.

07:46.900 --> 07:48.067
LOOK.

07:48.067 --> 07:50.367
AFTER WE BROKE UP,
WHEN YOU NEEDED TO TALK,

07:50.367 --> 07:51.700
I GAVE YOU THAT.

07:51.700 --> 07:54.333
I LET YOU GET WHATEVER YOU
HAD TO SAY OFF YOUR CHEST.

07:54.333 --> 07:56.133
NOW I NEED YOU TO DO
THE SAME FOR ME.

07:56.133 --> 07:58.600
FINE. BUT IT'S NOT HAPPENING
RIGHT NOW.

07:58.600 --> 08:00.600
I'LL MEET YOU
AT THE COFFEE SHOP TOMORROW.

08:00.600 --> 08:02.867
OKAY. THANK YOU, VAL.
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

08:02.867 --> 08:04.067
I JUST --

08:04.067 --> 08:05.267
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

08:05.267 --> 08:07.367
I GUESS I'LL FIND OUT
TOMORROW.

08:16.133 --> 08:18.833
KEISHA, REMEMBER WE USED
TO HAVE THAT OFF-THE-WALL,

08:18.833 --> 08:21.200
DON'T-STOP-TILL-YOU-GET-ENOUGH
KIND OF LOVE?

08:21.200 --> 08:22.433
YOU DON'T WANT THAT ANYMORE?

08:22.433 --> 08:24.933
WOODY,
IT'S NOT GOING TO HAPPEN.

08:24.933 --> 08:28.467
HOW CAN I BE YOUR BOY TOY
IF YOU WON'T PLAY WITH ME?

08:28.467 --> 08:30.267
COME ON, GIRL. I NEED YOU.

08:30.267 --> 08:32.533
[ SCOFFS ]
I'M IN A RELATIONSHIP NOW.

08:32.533 --> 08:34.300
YOU'RE IN A WHAT?

08:34.300 --> 08:36.200
A RELATIONSHIP?
WANT ME TO SPELL IT OUT?

08:36.200 --> 08:39.933
IT'S WHEN TWO PEOPLE ARE
EXCLUSIVE WITH ONE ANOTHER. HUH?

08:39.933 --> 08:41.700
I'VE BEEN IN ONE OF THOSE
SINCE I'VE KNOWN YOU,

08:41.700 --> 08:43.633
BUT I DROP EVERYTHING
WHENEVER YOU CALL.

08:43.633 --> 08:46.100
WHAT DOES THIS GUY HAVE
THAT I DON'T?

08:46.100 --> 08:47.767
I'VE ALREADY WOUNDED
YOUR EGO.

08:47.767 --> 08:50.300
NOW YOU WANT ME TO START IN
ON YOUR FEELINGS, TOO?

08:50.300 --> 08:53.433
DOES HE HAVE ALL THIS?

08:53.433 --> 08:57.467
***

08:57.467 --> 09:00.833
BOY...
PUT YOUR CLOTHES BACK ON.

09:00.833 --> 09:02.767
I'M OFF THE MARKET.

09:02.767 --> 09:04.267
[ GRUNTING SOFTLY ]

09:04.267 --> 09:05.933
[ GRUNTING LOUDER ]

09:05.933 --> 09:08.600
MMM.
[ CURTAIN RINGS RATTLE ]

09:08.600 --> 09:09.933
OHH.

09:09.933 --> 09:12.433
YOU KNOW IT'S WRONG TO LEAVE ME
ALL WORKED UP LIKE THIS.

09:12.433 --> 09:14.133
[ CURTAIN RINGS RATTLE ]

09:14.133 --> 09:15.200
YOU'RE RIGHT.

09:15.200 --> 09:17.100
OMAR!
[ CURTAIN RINGS RATTLE ]

09:17.100 --> 09:19.500
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
WE'LL PLAY IT YOUR WAY.

09:19.500 --> 09:21.367
BUT CALL ME THE MINUTE
HE MESSES UP,

09:21.367 --> 09:23.067
AND HE WILL MESS UP.

09:23.067 --> 09:25.967
PLEASE, GOD,
LET HIM MESS UP.

09:25.967 --> 09:27.433
BYE, WOODY.

09:27.433 --> 09:28.600
BYE-BYE.

09:28.600 --> 09:30.067
***

09:30.067 --> 09:33.700
I DON'T KNOW, OMAR. I THINK
THIS MIGHT BE A LITTLE TIGHT.

09:33.700 --> 09:34.800
YOU'RE WELCOME.

09:34.800 --> 09:35.833
EVERYBODY KNOWS
THE HOTTER THE BARTENDER,

09:35.833 --> 09:36.967
THE BETTER THE TIPS.

09:36.967 --> 09:38.267
YEAH, BUT IT'S JUST
TEMPORARY

09:38.267 --> 09:40.067
UNTIL I CAN ACTUALLY
PASS THE BAR.

09:40.067 --> 09:41.900
I KNOW, HONEY, BUT NO ONE
CAN SEE YOUR MIND,

09:41.900 --> 09:43.633
SO, IN THE MEANTIME,
SHOW 'EM SOME PECS.

09:43.633 --> 09:45.367
AND HERE I THOUGHT
YOU WERE WITH ME

09:45.367 --> 09:47.167
'CAUSE YOU WANTED
TO DATE A LAWYER.

09:47.167 --> 09:48.367
THAT'S THE FIRST TIME
IN TWO MONTHS

09:48.367 --> 09:50.200
YOU ACTUALLY USED
THE WORD "DATE."

09:50.200 --> 09:51.500
SO IS THAT
WHAT WE'RE DOING?

09:51.500 --> 09:53.600
I THINK IT'S SOMETHING
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT.

09:53.600 --> 09:55.267
LOOK, LET ME TAKE YOU
TO DINNER,

09:55.267 --> 09:57.533
SINCE LUNCH
IS ALMOST OVER.

09:57.533 --> 09:59.067
IT'S NOT GONNA BE
ONE OF THOSE

09:59.067 --> 10:01.033
"I LIKE YOU, BUT..." KINDS
OF DINNERS, IS IT?

10:01.033 --> 10:02.700
NO, NOT AT ALL.
IT'LL BE GOOD.

10:02.700 --> 10:06.033
I JUST WANNA MAKE SURE
WE'RE ON THE SAME PAGE.

10:06.033 --> 10:07.267
YOU'VE BEEN GONE
FOR OVER AN HOUR,

10:07.267 --> 10:09.933
AND NOW I CAN'T TAKE
MY LUNCH BREAK WITH VINCENT.

10:09.933 --> 10:12.700
VAL TEXTED ME TO PICK UP
SOME MATERIALS FOR HER.

10:12.700 --> 10:15.267
BUT IF I HAD KNOWN WHAT
YOU HAD ON THE MENU,

10:15.267 --> 10:16.767
I WOULD HAVE HURRIED BACK.

10:16.767 --> 10:17.867
FREAK.

10:17.867 --> 10:18.867
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

10:18.867 --> 10:20.333
UH, NO.
TONIGHT I HAVE THAT THING

10:20.333 --> 10:21.700
I CAN'T GET OUT OF,
REMEMBER?

10:21.700 --> 10:25.567
BUT TOMORROW, DEFINITELY.
OKAY?

10:25.567 --> 10:26.933
[ KISS ]

10:26.933 --> 10:32.267
***

10:32.267 --> 10:35.033
HE IS YUMMY.
WHERE'D YOU FIND HIM?

10:35.033 --> 10:36.433
DON'T TELL VAL, BUT...

10:36.433 --> 10:37.967
FOUND HIM AT THE GAP.

10:37.967 --> 10:41.167
WE WERE LOOKING FOR JEANS,
BUT WE ONLY SAW EACH OTHER.

10:41.167 --> 10:43.267
AND NOW THAT'S MY BOO.

10:43.267 --> 10:45.667
KINDA THOUGHT YOU WERE
A PLAYER.

10:45.667 --> 10:48.633
DIDN'T REALLY PICTURE YOU
AS A ONE-MAN MAN.

10:48.633 --> 10:51.967
THAT'S BECAUSE I WAS WAITING
ON THE RIGHT ONE.

10:51.967 --> 10:54.433
VINCENT'S FUN.
HE'S CULTURED,

10:54.433 --> 10:56.133
AND HE'S GONNA BE A LAWYER.
MMM.

10:56.133 --> 10:59.167
AND IF MY WASHING MACHINE
EVER BREAKS DOWN,

10:59.167 --> 11:01.700
I COULD DO MY LAUNDRY
ON HIS ABS.

11:01.700 --> 11:04.400
OKAY.

11:04.400 --> 11:06.867
ISN'T THAT THE PROFESSOR
YOU WENT DOWN UNDER WITH?

11:06.867 --> 11:08.400
WHAT DOES HE WANT NOW?

11:08.400 --> 11:10.333
THIS GUY'S REALLY PATHETIC.

11:10.333 --> 11:11.833
HE JUST CAN'T LET IT GO.

11:13.600 --> 11:15.333
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:15.333 --> 11:17.667
ARE YOU TRYING TO PRETEND
LIKE YOU'RE SHOPPING HERE?

11:17.667 --> 11:19.600
NO. I'VE HAD EVERYTHING
IN HERE

11:19.600 --> 11:21.167
THAT I COULD POSSIBLY WANT.

11:21.167 --> 11:23.567
BUT I CAME BY BECAUSE I WANTED
TO SEE THE LOOK ON YOUR FACE

11:23.567 --> 11:26.167
WHEN I TOLD YOU I WAS
FLUNKING YOU FOR THE SEMESTER.

11:26.167 --> 11:27.867
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

11:27.867 --> 11:29.267
IF YOU FLUNK ME, THEN I WON'T
BE IN A GOOD STANDING,

11:29.267 --> 11:30.667
AND I'LL LOSE MY VISA.

11:30.667 --> 11:32.167
I COULD BE DEPORTED.

11:32.167 --> 11:34.833
NOW THAT IS
A DISTINCT POSSIBILITY.

11:34.833 --> 11:36.467
I'LL GO TO THE DEAN,
AND I'LL TELL HER EVERYTHING.

11:36.467 --> 11:37.600
NOW, I FIGURED YOU WOULD,

11:37.600 --> 11:39.967
SO WHEN I HANDED IN
MY LETTER OF RESIGNATION

11:39.967 --> 11:41.967
THIS MORNING, I TOLD HER
YOU MIGHT BE COMING BY

11:41.967 --> 11:43.667
TO DISPUTE YOUR GRADE.

11:43.667 --> 11:47.133
I ALSO TOLD HER WHY.
HAVE A SAFE TRIP BACK.

11:51.233 --> 11:54.500
WHY DID I SLEEP WITH HIM?

11:54.500 --> 11:58.133
BABY, THAT'S THE TITLE
OF MY AUTOBIOGRAPHY.

12:05.567 --> 12:07.467
[ CLINK ]

12:14.600 --> 12:16.067
[ CLATTER ]

12:16.067 --> 12:18.167
[ CHAIR SCRAPES FLOOR ]

12:18.167 --> 12:19.533
I NEED YOU TO BE QUICK.

12:19.533 --> 12:20.967
I HAVE A BUSINESS TO RUN,

12:20.967 --> 12:23.233
AND YOU AND I HAVE
NO BUSINESS AT ALL.

12:23.233 --> 12:25.833
WELL, TO BE HONEST, I WASN'T
SURE IF YOU'D EVEN SHOW UP.

12:25.833 --> 12:27.900
AND I'M SORRY AGAIN
FOR COMING BY YOUR HOUSE

12:27.900 --> 12:28.967
UNANNOUNCED LIKE THAT.

12:28.967 --> 12:32.733
QUINN, SERIOUSLY.
SAY WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND.

12:32.733 --> 12:36.200
WELL...I KNOW THIS IS
GONNA SOUND STRANGE

12:36.200 --> 12:38.600
COMING FROM ME,
BUT I'VE BEEN IN COUNSELING,

12:38.600 --> 12:41.167
AND IT'S HELPED ME REALIZE
I WAS A FOOL TO LET YOU GO.

12:41.167 --> 12:42.867
IF I HAD TO DO IT
ALL OVER AGAIN,

12:42.867 --> 12:45.233
IF I COULD GO BACK
TO THAT NIGHT ON YOUR BALCONY,

12:45.233 --> 12:47.100
I WOULD MAKE
A DIFFERENT DECISION.

12:47.100 --> 12:50.400
MY LIFE HASN'T BEEN THE SAME
SINCE WE BROKE UP.

12:50.400 --> 12:52.933
I MEAN, YOU AND ME --
WE WERE GOOD TOGETHER.

12:52.933 --> 12:55.400
WE MADE A GREAT TEAM,
AND I WANT THAT BACK.

12:55.400 --> 12:58.433
I WANT YOU BACK.

12:58.433 --> 13:02.400
AND I'M TRULY SORRY FOR
EVERYTHING I PUT YOU THROUGH.

13:02.400 --> 13:04.633
CAN WE...

13:04.633 --> 13:07.200
PUT THE PAST BEHIND US
AND TRY AGAIN?

13:07.200 --> 13:10.500
[ LAUGHS ]

13:10.500 --> 13:13.267
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO LAUGH.

13:13.267 --> 13:16.433
I REALLY DIDN'T, OKAY?
IT WAS JUST...

13:16.433 --> 13:18.133
THIS MUST BE A JOKE.

13:18.133 --> 13:20.300
I'M DEAD SERIOUS, VAL.

13:20.300 --> 13:21.567
QUINN...

13:21.567 --> 13:26.067
THIS IS TOO LITTLE
AND WAY TOO LATE.

13:26.067 --> 13:29.533
I HAVE A BOYFRIEND NOW,
AND BESIDES,

13:29.533 --> 13:32.267
YOU HAD AMPLE TIME
TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT,

13:32.267 --> 13:33.733
AND YOU CHOSE NOT TO.

13:33.733 --> 13:37.133
OKAY. I HAD A FIANCÃ©E,
BUT I HANDLED THAT.

13:37.133 --> 13:39.200
YOU HANDLED THAT?

13:39.200 --> 13:44.367
I'M SORRY, BUT IF MY MEMORY
SERVES ME CORRECTLY,

13:44.367 --> 13:48.967
IT WAS SHELLEY WHO CALLED OFF
THE WEDDING AND LEFT YOU.

13:48.967 --> 13:50.067
OKAY, WHATEVER.

13:50.067 --> 13:52.167
THE POINT IS,
I'M HERE RIGHT NOW

13:52.167 --> 13:53.733
AND I'M BARING MY SOUL.

13:53.733 --> 13:57.067
EIGHT MONTHS AGO,
YOU WERE TRYING TO RUSH ME.

13:57.067 --> 13:59.167
YOU CAN'T RUSH A MAN INTO
MAKING A DECISION LIKE THAT.

13:59.167 --> 14:00.967
BUT I GOT HERE ON MY OWN,

14:00.967 --> 14:02.800
SO GIVE ME CREDIT
FOR STEPPING UP AND SAYING

14:02.800 --> 14:04.367
I DON'T WANNA THROW AWAY
WHAT WE HAD.

14:04.367 --> 14:06.433
I'M READY FOR YOU NOW.

14:06.433 --> 14:10.933
QUINN...IT IS SO OVER
BETWEEN YOU AND ME.

14:10.933 --> 14:16.233
DID YOU HEAR A WORD I SAID?
I AM WITH SOMEONE.

14:16.233 --> 14:19.133
AND IF YOU DON'T KNOW BY NOW
WHO THAT IS,

14:19.133 --> 14:22.900
LET ME BE THE ONE
TO TELL YOU.

14:22.900 --> 14:24.233
IT'S JERRY.

14:24.233 --> 14:26.900
JERRY WHO?

14:26.900 --> 14:28.100
WATERS.

14:28.100 --> 14:31.700
OF ALL THE DUDES
IN THE WORLD TO DATE,

14:31.700 --> 14:34.867
YOU PICKED THE OWNER
OF MY TEAM?

14:34.867 --> 14:37.467
HOW DO YOU THINK
THAT MAKES ME LOOK?

14:37.467 --> 14:41.100
[ HUFFS ] I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
HOW THAT MAKES YOU LOOK.

14:41.100 --> 14:43.467
THIS ISN'T ABOUT YOU.

14:43.467 --> 14:45.967
I HAVE ABSOLUTELY
NO CONSIDERATION FOR YOU

14:45.967 --> 14:49.200
WHEN IT COMES TO LIVING
MY LIFE.

14:49.200 --> 14:51.700
I WOULD HAVE NEVER
EXPECTED THIS FROM YOU.

14:53.633 --> 14:56.200
[ CHAIR SCRAPES FLOOR ]

14:56.200 --> 14:58.400
I KNOW I MESSED UP,

14:58.400 --> 14:59.733
BUT DAMN.

15:01.467 --> 15:03.567
YOU DON'T GET A DUDE BACK
LIKE THAT.

15:07.300 --> 15:08.300
[ SIGHS ]

15:08.300 --> 15:09.733
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:13.367 --> 15:14.933
Woman: * IF YOU WANT IT *

15:14.933 --> 15:17.333
I CAN'T BELIEVE
QUINN SAID ALL THAT.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.067
WHAT DID HE THINK,
THAT YOU WERE JUST GONNA

15:19.067 --> 15:21.767
SIT AROUND AND WAIT FOR HIM
TO HAVE HIS "AHA!" MOMENT?
PROBABLY.

15:21.767 --> 15:24.800
I'VE DEALT WITH MY FAIR SHARE
OF ATHLETES AND ENTERTAINERS,

15:24.800 --> 15:26.067
AND SOME OF THEIR EGOS

15:26.067 --> 15:28.333
ARE BIGGER THAN THE STADIUMS
THEY PLAY IN.

15:28.333 --> 15:30.767
BUT THEN AGAIN, SO WAS SOME
OF THEIR EQUIPMENT.

15:30.767 --> 15:32.433
I GUESS
IT'S NOT THEIR FAULT.

15:32.433 --> 15:34.633
WHAT THEY WANT IS EITHER
THROWN AT THEM OR THEY BUY IT.

15:34.633 --> 15:36.233
THEY DON'T HAVE TO TRY
TO EARN ANYTHING

15:36.233 --> 15:38.267
BECAUSE THEY THINK
THEY DESERVE EVERYTHING.

15:38.267 --> 15:40.767
HENCE, THE IGNORANCE
HE WAS SPEWING OUT TODAY.

15:40.767 --> 15:43.267
I'M GLAD YOU LAUGHED
IN HIS FACE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:43.267 --> 15:44.967
I DID IT BEFORE
I COULD STOP MYSELF.

15:44.967 --> 15:48.067
I FIND IT IRONIC THAT HE
PLAYS WITH BALLS FOR A LIVING

15:48.067 --> 15:49.833
BUT DIDN'T HAVE ANY TO MARRY ME.

15:49.833 --> 15:54.067
VAL, DON'T YELL AT ME,
BUT I HAVE A QUESTION.

15:54.067 --> 15:57.800
DID YOU EVEN FOR A FLICKER
OF A SECOND CONSIDER IT?

15:57.800 --> 15:58.933
Both: CONSIDER WHAT?

15:58.933 --> 16:00.700
WHOA! HEAR ME OUT.

16:00.700 --> 16:02.400
THIS WAS A GUY WHO,
NOT SO LONG AGO,

16:02.400 --> 16:03.667
YOU WERE MADLY IN LOVE WITH

16:03.667 --> 16:05.900
AND WANTED TO SPEND
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE WITH.

16:05.900 --> 16:08.833
I'M JUST ASKING,
DID IT STIR UP ANYTHING?

16:08.833 --> 16:10.167
HELL, NO.

16:10.167 --> 16:12.300
I DIDN'T FEEL A THING.

16:12.300 --> 16:14.433
I JUST WONDERED WHY MEN
HAVE TO LOSE YOU

16:14.433 --> 16:17.100
BEFORE THEY REALIZE
THAT YOU MEAN SOMETHING TO THEM.

16:17.100 --> 16:19.433
WOMEN DO THAT, TOO.
I SHOULD KNOW.

16:19.433 --> 16:21.800
TRUE, BUT WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT MEN RIGHT NOW,

16:21.800 --> 16:24.967
AND A LOT OF THEM THINK OF US
AS ACCESSORIES.

16:24.967 --> 16:27.367
IF WE'RE NOT THE WATCH THAT GOES
WITH THAT PARTICULAR SUIT,

16:27.367 --> 16:28.967
THEY JUST PICK ANOTHER ONE.

16:28.967 --> 16:30.700
WELL, I GUESS
HE FINALLY REMEMBERED

16:30.700 --> 16:34.500
THAT I AM THE CLASSIC PIECE
THAT GOES WITH EVERYTHING.

16:34.500 --> 16:37.067
SOMETIMES PEOPLE HAVE TO LEARN
A HARD LESSON,

16:37.067 --> 16:38.833
AND QUINN'S HARD LESSON
IS YOU.

16:38.833 --> 16:40.400
YES.

16:40.400 --> 16:42.333
FOR THE REST OF HIS LIFE,
HE WILL ALWAYS KNOW

16:42.333 --> 16:45.400
YOU ARE THE ONE
WHO GOT AWAY.

16:45.400 --> 16:49.400
I KNOW THIS SOUNDS MEAN,
BUT AFTER ALL HE PUT ME THROUGH,

16:49.400 --> 16:52.067
I CAN'T THINK
OF A BETTER OUTCOME.

16:52.067 --> 16:54.833
I CAN. IT INVOLVES US
GOING TO A GAME

16:54.833 --> 16:58.067
AND CHEERING FOR
ALL THE POINTS HE'S MAKING

16:58.067 --> 16:59.300
FROM THE BENCH.

16:59.300 --> 17:00.600
OH!
RIGHT?

17:00.600 --> 17:02.700
[ LAUGHS ]

17:12.867 --> 17:15.167
OH, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU'D BE HOME SO EARLY.

17:15.167 --> 17:16.300
I'LL GO GET DRESSED.

17:16.300 --> 17:19.167
IT'S OKAY.

17:20.867 --> 17:22.300
[ SIGHS ]

17:22.300 --> 17:23.867
WHY DO GUYS DO THAT?

17:23.867 --> 17:25.567
DO WHAT?

17:25.567 --> 17:26.867
GET OUT OF THE SHOWER

17:26.867 --> 17:28.100
AND SIT ON THE COUCH
IN A WET TOWEL

17:28.100 --> 17:30.167
AND EAT A BOWL OF CEREAL.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:30.167 --> 17:31.200
MY HUSBAND,
AS UPTIGHT AS HE WAS,

17:31.200 --> 17:32.467
USED TO DO THE SAME THING.

17:32.467 --> 17:35.233
YOU KNOW, IT'S SAFE TO SAY
WE'RE FRIENDS NOW, RIGHT?

17:35.233 --> 17:36.233
YEAH.

17:36.233 --> 17:37.533
HOW COME THIS IS
THE FIRST TIME

17:37.533 --> 17:38.600
YOU'VE EVER SAID
ANYTHING PERSONAL

17:38.600 --> 17:39.900
ABOUT YOU OR YOUR HUSBAND?

17:39.900 --> 17:42.600
WHY DON'T YOU EVER TALK ABOUT
WHAT HAPPENED WITH YOU GUYS?

17:42.600 --> 17:43.900
BECAUSE IT'S HARD.

17:43.900 --> 17:45.233
BESIDES, IF YOU'VE BEEN

17:45.233 --> 17:47.633
WATCHING THE NEWS RECENTLY,
YOU'D KNOW ALL ABOUT US.

17:47.633 --> 17:50.367
WELL, I'M ASKING YOU,
NOT THE NEWS.

17:50.367 --> 17:53.767
MAYBE YOU'VE NEVER BEEN THROUGH
ANYTHING LIKE THIS BEFORE,

17:53.767 --> 17:59.700
BUT...IT'S KIND OF LIKE
A WOUND THAT WON'T HEAL.

17:59.700 --> 18:00.900
WHEN I TALK ABOUT IT,

18:00.900 --> 18:02.633
I FEEL LIKE IT'S HAPPENING
ALL OVER AGAIN.

18:02.633 --> 18:04.800
I'VE BEEN THROUGH
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.
YEAH?

18:04.800 --> 18:07.367
BIG-TIME, YEAH.

18:07.367 --> 18:09.867
I WAS 19 WHEN I GOT FAMOUS.

18:09.867 --> 18:14.100
IT WAS GIRLS, DRUGS.
PARTIES WERE EVERYWHERE.

18:14.100 --> 18:16.533
THEN I GOT LOST IN IT ALL.

18:16.533 --> 18:18.833
EMBARRASSED THE GROUP,
EMBARRASSED MY FAMILY,

18:18.833 --> 18:20.200
EMBARRASSED MYSELF.

18:20.200 --> 18:23.133
EVERY MISTAKE I MADE
WAS ON TMZ OR YouTube.

18:23.133 --> 18:24.733
I KNOW THEY'RE JUST
DOING THEIR JOBS,

18:24.733 --> 18:27.533
BUT THE PRESS CAN BE
SO HEARTLESS.

18:27.533 --> 18:28.967
YEAH, THEY MAY HAVE FIRED
THE GUN,

18:28.967 --> 18:30.833
BUT I'M THE ONE THAT KEPT
GIVING THEM THE AMMO

18:30.833 --> 18:32.267
AND PUTTING THE TARGET
ON MY BACK.

18:32.267 --> 18:34.700
WHY ARE WE TALKING
AND NOT WRITING THIS DOWN?

18:34.700 --> 18:36.100
THIS IS THE TYPE OF STUFF

18:36.100 --> 18:38.133
THAT WE SHOULD BE PUTTING
IN A SONG.

18:38.133 --> 18:39.533
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

18:39.533 --> 18:40.967
[ Mouth full ]
HOLD MY FOOD.

18:40.967 --> 18:42.467
OH! [ LAUGHS ] OKAY.

18:42.467 --> 18:44.600
MM. ALL RIGHT.
[ PLAYING CHORDS ]

18:44.600 --> 18:46.467
GET THE BEAT, GET THE BEAT.
OKAY. [ HUMMING ]

18:46.467 --> 18:48.600
SO... [ HUMMING ]
YOU HEAR THAT?
NICE. UH-HUH.

18:48.600 --> 18:49.933
YOU FEEL THAT ONE. RIGHT.
UH-HUH.

18:49.933 --> 18:51.067
I FEEL IT. OKAY.
[ GRUNTS ]

18:51.067 --> 18:53.833
* I WAS FAMOUS AS A TEEN *

18:53.833 --> 18:55.867
* YOU SAW ME IN MAGAZINES *

18:55.867 --> 18:57.567
[ LAUGHS ]
* OH, OH *

18:57.567 --> 18:59.600
* I WAS SUPER,
SUPER HANDSOME *
OKAY, MY TURN, MY TURN.

18:59.600 --> 19:02.367
UM... * HEADLINE NEWS *

19:02.367 --> 19:04.633
* ALWAYS GIVING ME
THE BLUES *

19:04.633 --> 19:05.833
YO!
[ LAUGHS ]

19:05.833 --> 19:08.100
KEEP IT GOING,
KEEP IT GOING.
UM...

19:08.100 --> 19:10.100
ARE YOU GETTING BEER?
YEAH.

19:10.100 --> 19:11.333
I LOVE YOU. UM...

19:11.333 --> 19:13.333
* AND I'M... *

19:13.333 --> 19:23.533
[ HUMMING ]

19:23.533 --> 19:26.067
* I DON'T WANNA BE ALONE *

19:26.067 --> 19:28.067
NICE!
[ LAUGHS ]

19:30.300 --> 19:34.067
[ CAR DOORS CLOSE ]

19:34.067 --> 19:35.500
HI, LADIES!

19:35.500 --> 19:37.967
WELCOME TO MY BRUNCH.

19:37.967 --> 19:39.833
SO IS THIS THE NEW CAR
MALCOLM BOUGHT YOU?

19:39.833 --> 19:41.233
I AM SO JEALOUS.

19:41.233 --> 19:44.067
YOU SHOULD BE. HE EVEN GOT
MY INITIALS PUT IN THE SEATS.

19:44.067 --> 19:46.400
WHAT DO YOU DO TO MEN THAT
MAKES THEM SO CRAZY ABOUT YOU?

19:46.400 --> 19:48.667
I COULD TELL YOU, BUT THEN
I'D HAVE TO KILL YOU.

19:48.667 --> 19:50.067
[ ALL LAUGH ]

19:50.067 --> 19:52.933
SORRY WE'RE LATE.
APRIL OVERSLEPT.

19:52.933 --> 19:55.900
SHE WAS UP ALL NIGHT MAKING
SWEET MUSIC WITH REED.

19:55.900 --> 19:58.867
OHH. REAL MUSIC
OR SEX MUSIC?

19:58.867 --> 20:01.867
REAL MUSIC. TECHNICALLY,
I'M STILL MARRIED, REMEMBER?

20:01.867 --> 20:02.900
[ SCOFFS ]

20:02.900 --> 20:04.533
Valerie:
SHE PRACTICALLY SAW HIM NAKED.

20:04.533 --> 20:08.100
[ GASPS ] WELL, DID YOUR EYES
AT LEAST GET SOME?

20:08.100 --> 20:10.267
OR ARE THEY TECHNICALLY
STILL MARRIED, TOO?

20:10.267 --> 20:11.567
HE HAD ON A TOWEL
AND A TANK TOP.

20:11.567 --> 20:13.500
THAT HARDLY COUNTS AS NAKED.

20:13.500 --> 20:15.200
BUT HE'S STILL PRETTY HOT.

20:15.200 --> 20:17.833
HOWEVER, I AM NOT GOING THERE.

20:17.833 --> 20:20.533
YOU WEAR
THIS MANSION WELL.

20:20.533 --> 20:23.033
I KNOW.
IT'S JUST MY SIZE.

20:23.033 --> 20:24.933
AND IT SMELLS GREAT
IN HERE.

20:24.933 --> 20:27.533
KEISHA, YOU GET AN "A"
FOR EFFORT ALREADY.

20:27.533 --> 20:30.200
THAT'S MY PRALINE FRENCH TOAST
CASSEROLE.

20:30.200 --> 20:31.700
DON'T ASK.

20:31.700 --> 20:33.700
I GOT THE RECIPE
FROM PAULA DEEN.

20:33.700 --> 20:35.867
SO IF YOU DON'T LIKE IT,
E-MAIL HER.

20:35.867 --> 20:37.900
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

20:37.900 --> 20:40.467
***

20:40.467 --> 20:42.767
THIS IS MALCOLM'S FATHER,
MR. FRANKS.

20:42.767 --> 20:46.867
JUST WANNA LET YOU TWO KNOW
UPFRONT THAT I'M SPOKEN FOR.

20:46.867 --> 20:48.533
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
Malcolm: BY WHO, POPS?

20:48.533 --> 20:50.633
I'LL TELL YOU...
AS SOON AS THESE

20:50.633 --> 20:53.267
BEAUTIFUL YOUNG LADIES
INTRODUCE THEMSELVES.

20:53.267 --> 20:54.333
I'M APRIL.

20:54.333 --> 20:56.100
AND I'M VAL.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

20:56.100 --> 20:59.533
DO PRETTY WOMEN ALWAYS
HANG OUT IN GROUPS?

20:59.533 --> 21:01.733
THE CONFUSION YOU MUST
CAUSE ALL THE MEN --

21:01.733 --> 21:04.400
I MEAN, WHO DO YOU
FLIRT WITH FIRST?

21:04.400 --> 21:05.600
[ WOMEN LAUGH ]

21:05.600 --> 21:08.433
WELL, I SEE WHERE MALCOLM GETS
HIS GIFT OF GAB.

21:08.433 --> 21:10.500
DON'T YOU, KEISHA?

21:10.500 --> 21:11.600
THEY ARE DOUBLE TROUBLE
FOR SURE.

21:11.600 --> 21:13.400
OH, PLEASE DON'T PUMP
HIS HEAD UP.

21:13.400 --> 21:15.433
I DIDN'T GET IT FROM HIM.
HE LEARNED FROM ME.

21:15.433 --> 21:16.733
AS MUCH AS WE ENJOY

21:16.733 --> 21:19.367
WATCHING TWO HANDSOME MEN
FIGHT FOR OUR ATTENTION,

21:19.367 --> 21:21.967
IT'S TIME TO EAT.

21:21.967 --> 21:24.600
I LOVE TO EAT. [ LAUGHS ]

21:24.600 --> 21:26.267
WHAT'S UP, MALCOLM?

21:26.267 --> 21:28.067
I GUESS MY INVITATION
GOT LOST IN THE MAIL.

21:31.433 --> 21:33.267
EVERYBODY...

21:33.267 --> 21:36.100
THIS IS
MY LITTLE BROTHER TERRENCE.

21:36.100 --> 21:37.433
[ PALMS SLAP ]

21:37.433 --> 21:41.067
[ Lowered voice ] WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

21:44.933 --> 21:46.500
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

21:46.500 --> 21:48.367
I'M HERE TO SEE
MY BIG BROTHER.

21:48.367 --> 21:49.800
TANYA SAID
SHE COULDN'T MAKE IT,

21:49.800 --> 21:51.800
SO I FIGURED YOU MIGHT WANT
A LITTLE MORE FAMILY

21:51.800 --> 21:53.933
AT YOUR FAMILY BRUNCH.

21:59.367 --> 22:02.600
[ Lowered voice ]
DID YOU KNOW ABOUT THIS?

22:02.600 --> 22:04.200
[ Lowered voice ]
WELL, YOUR SISTER

22:04.200 --> 22:06.167
SAID SHE MIGHT MENTION IT
TO HIM.

22:06.167 --> 22:09.167
I WAS HOPING IF HE CAME,
YOU TWO WOULD WORK THINGS OUT.

22:09.167 --> 22:11.300
THE FEUD'S GONE ON TOO LONG,
MALCOLM.

22:11.300 --> 22:13.533
HEY, POPS. YOU MISS ME?

22:13.533 --> 22:16.200
GIVE ME A HUG, BOY!
[ LAUGHS ]

22:16.200 --> 22:18.200
NOW I RAISED YOU
TO BE A GENTLEMAN,

22:18.200 --> 22:20.067
AND THERE ARE WOMEN
IN THE ROOM.

22:20.067 --> 22:23.100
I SEE. HELLO, GORGEOUS.

22:23.100 --> 22:26.067
THIS IS MY GIRLFRIEND...

22:26.067 --> 22:28.733
KEISHA.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

22:28.733 --> 22:29.867
YOU, TOO, KEISHA.

22:29.867 --> 22:31.433
AND THIS IS VAL,
AND THAT'S APRIL.

22:31.433 --> 22:34.700
APRIL.

22:34.700 --> 22:36.467
I KNOW
WHERE I WANNA SIT.

22:41.333 --> 22:44.133
Keisha:
I CAN TELL YOU'RE NOT OKAY.

22:44.133 --> 22:46.167
IS THERE ANYTHING I CAN DO?

22:46.167 --> 22:48.933
NO.
PLEASE DON'T DO ANYTHING.

22:48.933 --> 22:51.900
JUST...LET ME HANDLE
MY BROTHER.

22:51.900 --> 22:54.667
OKAY, YOU'RE THE BOSS.

22:54.667 --> 22:55.700
HMM.

22:55.700 --> 22:57.633
I JUST SAID THAT
TO MAKE YOU SMILE.

22:57.633 --> 23:00.067
DON'T GET ALL HAPPY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:06.767 --> 23:09.467
SO, UH, APRIL, YOU IN
THE MUSIC BUSINESS, HUH?

23:09.467 --> 23:11.733
I GOT A COUPLE BOYS I MET
ON THE INSIDE THAT RAP.

23:11.733 --> 23:14.233
MAYBE WHEN THEY GET OUT,
YOU CAN HOOK 'EM UP.

23:14.233 --> 23:17.233
WELL... [ CLEARS THROAT ]
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

23:17.233 --> 23:19.233
HEY, VAL,
WHASSUP WITH YOU?

23:19.233 --> 23:20.967
[ CHUCKLES ] YOU GOT A MAN?

23:20.967 --> 23:22.967
MM, YEP, I DO.

23:22.967 --> 23:26.167
AND I'M REALLY DEVOTED TO HIM,
TOO. THANKS, THOUGH.

23:26.167 --> 23:28.967
HE AIN'T THAT DEVOTED TO YOU,
OR ELSE HE'D BE HERE.

23:28.967 --> 23:31.267
[ CHUCKLES ] SO WHY DON'T YOU
GIVE ME YOUR NUMBER?

23:31.267 --> 23:32.600
I MEAN, I CAN TELL YOU NEED

23:32.600 --> 23:34.833
A LITTLE THUG PASSION
IN YOUR LIFE.
[ VALERIE GIGGLES ]

23:34.833 --> 23:37.667
EVERYBODY, DIDN'T KEISHA DO
A WONDERFUL JOB ON THE BRUNCH?

23:37.667 --> 23:39.667
MALCOLM AND I WANTED YOU
TO KNOW

23:39.667 --> 23:42.333
THAT WE DIDN'T FALL
OFF THE FACE OF THE EARTH,

23:42.333 --> 23:45.667
SO WE FIGURED IF WE DISTRACT YOU
WITH SOME GOOD FOOD,

23:45.667 --> 23:47.133
YOU'LL FORGIVE US
FOR DISAPPEARING.

23:47.133 --> 23:48.133
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:48.133 --> 23:49.600
WELL, NOW I UNDERSTAND.

23:49.600 --> 23:52.667
I MEAN, I WAS ABOUT TO START
TAKING IT PERSONAL

23:52.667 --> 23:54.267
THAT YOU WEREN'T
RETURNING MY PHONE CALLS.

23:54.267 --> 23:57.233
I THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU WERE UNHAPPY

23:57.233 --> 24:00.067
THAT YOUR BABY BROTHER
WAS OUT OF JAIL, BUT, UH,

24:00.067 --> 24:01.200
WE STILL NEED TO TAKE CARE

24:01.200 --> 24:02.333
OF THE UNFINISHED BUSINESS
WE GOT.

24:02.333 --> 24:04.467
NOW IS NOT THE TIME FOR THAT,
SON.

24:04.467 --> 24:06.433
YEAH, I'M NOT TALKING BUSINESS
RIGHT NOW, T.

24:06.433 --> 24:08.467
THERE'S NOT A LOT
TO TALK ABOUT.

24:08.467 --> 24:10.300
YOU CAN JUST BUY ME OUT TODAY,
MAN.

24:10.300 --> 24:11.733
THIS CONVERSATION
CAN BE OVER.

24:11.733 --> 24:14.733
WE CAN MAKE THIS
REALLY SIMPLE.

24:14.733 --> 24:17.567
WOULD ANYBODY ELSE LIKE SECONDS
OR SOMETHING ELSE TO DRINK?

24:17.567 --> 24:19.200
YOU GUYS TELL ME.

24:19.200 --> 24:21.700
IF YOU HAD TURNED
A MOM-AND-POP JEWELRY STORE

24:21.700 --> 24:24.967
INTO AN INTERNATIONAL OPERATION

24:24.967 --> 24:27.633
WORTH TENS OF MILLIONS
OF DOLLARS,

24:27.633 --> 24:31.533
IF YOU HAD A BROTHER LIKE ME
WHO HAD JUST GOTTEN OUT,

24:31.533 --> 24:32.767
WOULD YOU STOP HIM
FROM GETTING THE MONEY

24:32.767 --> 24:34.167
THAT'S RIGHTFULLY HIS?

24:34.167 --> 24:36.733
UH, TERRENCE,

24:36.733 --> 24:40.300
MAYBE YOU AND MALCOLM SHOULD
TALK ABOUT THIS IN PRIVATE.

24:40.300 --> 24:42.167
HEY, MAYBE YOU SHOULD STAY
OUT OF FAMILY BUSINESS.

24:42.167 --> 24:43.467
I WASN'T TALKING TO YOU.

24:43.467 --> 24:45.067
I LET YOU
DISRUPT MY BRUNCH,

24:45.067 --> 24:46.533
BUT YOU AIN'T
DISRESPECTING MY GIRL.

24:46.533 --> 24:48.233
I'M THE ONE BEING DISRESPECTED!

24:48.233 --> 24:51.167
I DID TIME FOR YOUR ASS!

24:51.167 --> 24:53.067
AND THIS IS HOW YOU TREAT ME?

24:53.067 --> 24:55.667
[ NAPKIN HITS TABLE ]
ALL RIGHT, BOYS. IT'S OVER.

24:55.667 --> 24:57.300
LADIES, I APOLOGIZE.

24:57.300 --> 25:00.467
I'LL CALL YOU IN THE MORNING,
MALCOLM. TERRENCE, LET'S GO.

25:00.467 --> 25:01.567
[ HUFFS ]

25:11.067 --> 25:12.900
TERRENCE!

25:12.900 --> 25:14.067
I SAID LET'S GO.

25:23.133 --> 25:25.567
THANK YOU FOR STANDING UP
FOR ME, BABE.

25:25.567 --> 25:26.833
YOU KNOW SOMETHING?

25:26.833 --> 25:28.200
IF YOU HAD JUST STAYED OUT OF IT
LIKE I TOLD YOU TO,

25:28.200 --> 25:29.933
THIS NEVER WOULD HAVE
HAPPENED.

25:29.933 --> 25:31.800
NEXT TIME, LISTEN.

25:35.200 --> 25:36.367
HE'S JUST UPSET.

25:36.367 --> 25:39.400
AND I'M JUST LEAVING.
LET'S GO.

25:47.633 --> 25:50.900
OH.
THAT WAS REALLY INTENSE.

25:50.900 --> 25:52.900
I FEEL BAD. IT WAS YOUR FIRST
GET-TOGETHER WITH MALCOLM,

25:52.900 --> 25:56.267
NOT TO MENTION I WAS LOVING
THAT FRENCH TOAST CASSEROLE.

25:56.267 --> 25:57.733
PAULA DEEN.

25:57.733 --> 26:01.900
SO WHAT IS THE BEEF
BETWEEN HIM AND HIS BROTHER?

26:01.900 --> 26:04.133
YOUR GUESS IS AS GOOD
AS MINE.

26:04.133 --> 26:06.400
HE RARELY TALKS
ABOUT HIS PAST.

26:06.400 --> 26:08.333
COME TO THINK OF IT,
I'VE TOLD HIM

26:08.333 --> 26:10.267
MORE ABOUT MINE THAN
HE'S EVER TOLD ME ABOUT HIS.

26:10.267 --> 26:12.933
WELL, YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES

26:12.933 --> 26:14.533
IT'S HARD FOR YOU
TO FIND THE "OFF" SWITCH.

26:14.533 --> 26:18.667
IT'S LIKE PLAYING
DOUBLE DUTCH.

26:18.667 --> 26:20.467
WE ARE CONSTANTLY TRYING
TO FIND THE TIME

26:20.467 --> 26:22.267
TO, LIKE, JUMP IN.

26:22.267 --> 26:24.667
I STOP AND LISTEN.

26:24.667 --> 26:25.733
SOMETIMES.

26:25.733 --> 26:28.800
BUT STILL, HE'S SO GUARDED
AND SECRETIVE

26:28.800 --> 26:30.400
ABOUT A LOT OF THINGS.

26:30.400 --> 26:31.600
HE'S A MAN.

26:31.600 --> 26:33.233
THEY DON'T TALK.
THEY KEEP EVERYTHING LOCKED UP.

26:33.233 --> 26:34.633
UNTIL THEY DON'T.

26:34.633 --> 26:38.967
AND THEN THEY VOMIT THEIR CRAP
ALL OVER YOU, LIKE QUINN.

26:38.967 --> 26:41.300
YOU HAVEN'T HEARD FROM HIM
AGAIN, HAVE YOU?
MNH-MNH.

26:41.300 --> 26:42.433
HE'S PRETTY PISSED.

26:42.433 --> 26:44.800
I DON'T THINK HE'LL BE
CALLING ME ANYMORE.

26:44.800 --> 26:46.500
DID YOU TELL JERRY ABOUT IT?
NOT YET.

26:46.500 --> 26:49.600
I HAVEN'T DECIDED IF
IT'S WORTH MENTIONING OR NOT.

26:49.600 --> 26:50.933
IT'S NOT.
WHY NOT?

26:50.933 --> 26:53.333
IF HE FINDS OUT LATER,
IT COULD MAKE THINGS WEIRD.

26:53.333 --> 26:55.567
WE'RE SITTING HERE TALKING
ABOUT GUYS NOT BEING HONEST

26:55.567 --> 26:56.767
AND NOT COMMUNICATING,

26:56.767 --> 26:58.933
AND YOU'RE TELLING VAL
TO DO THE SAME THING.

26:58.933 --> 27:00.900
APRIL,
MEN HOLD EVERYTHING IN

27:00.900 --> 27:03.233
BECAUSE THEY DON'T
WANNA LOOK FRAGILE.

27:03.233 --> 27:05.200
WOMEN HOLD
CERTAIN THINGS BACK

27:05.200 --> 27:06.800
SO MEN WON'T FIND OUT
WE ALREADY KNOW

27:06.800 --> 27:09.067
HOW FRAGILE THEY ARE.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

27:09.067 --> 27:11.900
WE ARE WALKING GODDESSES,

27:11.900 --> 27:16.067
AND THEY DO NOT DESERVE US,
PERIOD.

27:16.067 --> 27:17.433
[ CLINK ]

27:17.433 --> 27:19.533
[ ALL CHUCKLE ]

27:26.200 --> 27:29.067
SO WE WILL EXPECT
THOSE DELIVERIES NEXT WEEK.

27:29.067 --> 27:31.067
THANK YOU.

27:32.600 --> 27:35.133
THOUGHT YOU WERE LATE
FOR YOUR LUNCH WITH JERRY.

27:35.133 --> 27:37.067
I AM. I'M LEAVING NOW.

27:37.067 --> 27:38.500
HAVE YOU TALKED TO MALCOLM?

27:38.500 --> 27:40.533
I'M GONNA CALL HIM
A LITTLE LATER.

27:40.533 --> 27:42.400
WE BOTH NEED TO JUST
COOL OFF.

27:42.400 --> 27:43.467
THERE'S A CUSTOMER
IN THE FITTING ROOM.

27:43.467 --> 27:44.700
I WAS GONNA HELP HIM
BEFORE I LEFT,

27:44.700 --> 27:47.733
BUT HE SPECIFICALLY
ASKED FOR YOU.

27:47.733 --> 27:50.067
IS IT WOODY?
IF THIS KEEPS HAPPENING,

27:50.067 --> 27:52.333
I MIGHT HAVE TO REGISTER
MY KITTY CAT

27:52.333 --> 27:53.900
WITH THE POLICE DEPARTMENT.

27:53.900 --> 27:56.567
SHE'S TURNING OUT TO BE
QUITE A WEAPON.

27:56.567 --> 28:00.367
WELL, NO. THIS GUY
ACTUALLY LOOKS LIKE

28:00.367 --> 28:02.433
HE COULD ACTUALLY AFFORD
TO BUY SOMETHING.

28:02.433 --> 28:04.267
AH.

28:04.267 --> 28:05.800
MAY I HELP YOU?

28:05.800 --> 28:07.200
[ CURTAIN RINGS RATTLE ]

28:09.533 --> 28:12.733
I HOPE SO.

28:12.733 --> 28:15.100
YOU SEE, I'M IN
A TERRIBLE PREDICAMENT,

28:15.100 --> 28:16.733
AND WHEN I TOLD
THE OTHER SALESGIRL MY PROBLEM,

28:16.733 --> 28:18.933
SHE SAID THAT YOU WOULD BE

28:18.933 --> 28:20.767
THE PERFECT PERSON
TO HELP ME OUT.

28:20.767 --> 28:22.433
WHY IS THAT?

28:22.433 --> 28:24.300
I'M IN TROUBLE
WITH MY GIRLFRIEND,

28:24.300 --> 28:25.933
AND I NEED TO FIGURE OUT
A WAY TO LET HER KNOW

28:25.933 --> 28:27.567
HOW SORRY I AM.

28:27.567 --> 28:30.767
YOU CAN'T JUST SAY
YOU'RE SORRY?
NO, NO. SHE'S...

28:30.767 --> 28:33.200
HIGH-MAINTENANCE.
A SIMPLE "SORRY" WON'T CUT IT.

28:33.200 --> 28:34.500
IF YOU WERE MY GIRLFRIEND,

28:34.500 --> 28:39.267
HOW ELSE COULD I LET YOU KNOW
HOW SORRY I REALLY AM?

28:39.267 --> 28:40.633
YOU CAN EXPLAIN WHY ME
HAVING YOUR BACK

28:40.633 --> 28:42.333
WAS THE WRONG THING TO DO.

28:42.333 --> 28:43.533
IT WASN'T WRONG,

28:43.533 --> 28:45.100
BUT I HAD ALREADY ASKED YOU
TO LET ME HANDLE IT.

28:45.100 --> 28:48.167
BUT YOU WOULDN'T HAVE TO HANDLE
EVERYTHING BY YOURSELF

28:48.167 --> 28:50.133
IF YOU LET ME IN.

28:50.133 --> 28:53.667
OKAY. I'M NOT PROUD OF IT,
BUT...

28:53.667 --> 28:55.667
A LONG TIME AGO, ME AND TERRENCE
USED TO STEAL CARS

28:55.667 --> 28:57.467
AND SELL THEM
TO A CHOP SHOP.

28:57.467 --> 29:00.067
WE WERE KNUCKLEHEADS,
AND WE MADE GOOD MONEY

29:00.067 --> 29:01.800
UNTIL MY FATHER GAVE US
AN ULTIMATUM --

29:01.800 --> 29:03.233
GO TO SCHOOL
OR JOIN THE MILITARY.

29:03.233 --> 29:04.300
I CAN'T PICTURE YOU

29:04.300 --> 29:05.733
IN THE MILITARY,
TAKING ORDERS.

29:05.733 --> 29:06.800
AND NEITHER COULD I.

29:06.800 --> 29:08.167
AND THAT'S EXACTLY WHY
I SMARTENED UP

29:08.167 --> 29:09.500
AND WENT TO COLLEGE.

29:09.500 --> 29:12.233
NOW YOU KNOW WITHIN FIVE YEARS
OF TAKING OVER FOR MY POP,

29:12.233 --> 29:14.367
WE WENT FROM ONE STORE
IN ATLANTA

29:14.367 --> 29:16.267
TO BRANCHES
IN BEVERLY HILLS,

29:16.267 --> 29:18.500
NEW YORK, ZURICH,
PARIS, AND DUBAI.

29:18.500 --> 29:20.100
SO YOU WERE THE HERO,

29:20.100 --> 29:22.700
BUT TERRENCE
MADE ANOTHER CHOICE.

29:22.700 --> 29:25.267
AND, UNFORTUNATELY,
IT CAUGHT UP TO HIM.

29:25.267 --> 29:27.133
NOW WHEN THE D.A.
FINALLY BUSTED HIM,

29:27.133 --> 29:28.900
THEY OFFERED TO REDUCE
HIS SENTENCE

29:28.900 --> 29:31.633
IF HE WOULD GIVE UP
HIS PARTNERS,

29:31.633 --> 29:33.067
PAST AND PRESENT.

29:33.067 --> 29:34.167
BUT HE WOULDN'T.

29:34.167 --> 29:35.867
HE TOLD THEM TO GO TO HELL.

29:35.867 --> 29:40.400
SO...IN HIS MIND, HE DID
THE TIME FOR BOTH OF US,

29:40.400 --> 29:42.133
AND NOW HE WANTS ME
TO PAY HIM FOR IT.

29:42.133 --> 29:44.133
IT DOES KINDA SOUNDS
LIKE YOU OWE HIM, BABE.

29:44.133 --> 29:45.867
AND IF THERE WASN'T
MORE TO THE STORY,

29:45.867 --> 29:47.167
YOU'D BE RIGHT.

29:47.167 --> 29:49.100
NOW I CAN'T PROVE IT,
BUT IN MY GUT,

29:49.100 --> 29:51.100
I KNOW THAT WHEN I WAS
AWAY AT SCHOOL,

29:51.100 --> 29:53.900
TERRENCE ARRANGED TO HAVE
MY POP'S JEWELRY STORE ROBBED,

29:53.900 --> 29:55.933
AND EVEN THOUGH NO ONE
WAS HURT IN THE ROBBERY,

29:55.933 --> 29:58.267
MY POPS HAD GOTTEN SICK

29:58.267 --> 30:00.367
AND DIDN'T UPDATE
THE INSURANCE POLICY,

30:00.367 --> 30:01.600
SO THE FINANCIAL LOSS

30:01.600 --> 30:03.900
ALMOST DESTROYED OUR FAMILY
AND THE BUSINESS.

30:03.900 --> 30:05.600
DOES YOUR FATHER THINK
HE DID IT, TOO?

30:05.600 --> 30:06.633
HE HAS NO IDEA,

30:06.633 --> 30:08.900
AND I'VE BEEN HIDING
MY SUSPICIONS.

30:08.900 --> 30:13.500
BUT...THAT'S ANOTHER
CONVERSATION FOR ANOTHER TIME.

30:13.500 --> 30:14.533
RIGHT NOW
I JUST WANNA MAKE SURE

30:14.533 --> 30:16.933
ME AND MY GIRLFRIEND
ARE OKAY.

30:18.700 --> 30:21.467
THE HOUSE...

30:21.467 --> 30:23.833
IS BIG ENOUGH, SO...

30:23.833 --> 30:28.400
NEXT TIME YOU GET MAD AT ME,
JUST GO OVER TO THE OTHER SIDE.

30:28.400 --> 30:30.300
YOU DON'T EVER
HAVE TO LEAVE.

30:30.300 --> 30:33.900
NOW HOW'S THAT
FOR AN APOLOGY?

30:33.900 --> 30:36.100
PRETTY DAMN GOOD.

30:38.733 --> 30:41.800
[ KISS ]

30:41.800 --> 30:43.667
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:45.867 --> 30:47.100
IT HURTS LIKE HELL
WHEN I PUSH OFF.

30:47.100 --> 30:48.133
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO GO
AS HARD AS YOU CAN.

30:48.133 --> 30:50.633
HELL, I-I CAN TRY TO --

30:53.333 --> 30:54.367
I'LL MEET YOU ON THE COURT.
OKAY.

30:54.367 --> 30:55.933
VAL. VAL, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT.

30:55.933 --> 30:57.300
I AM HERE TO HAVE LUNCH
WITH JERRY.

30:57.300 --> 30:58.967
I DON'T WANNA BE LATE.

30:58.967 --> 31:00.767
WELL, BUT IT'S JUST
GONNA TAKE A SECOND, PLEASE.

31:00.767 --> 31:03.067
COME HERE, COME HERE.
LISTEN, LISTEN, LISTEN.

31:03.067 --> 31:05.500
MY AGENT JUST CONFIRMED
THAT YOUR BOYFRIEND

31:05.500 --> 31:07.333
IS ABOUT TO SEND ME
OVER TO WASHINGTON.

31:07.333 --> 31:09.100
SO WHAT DOES THAT HAVE
TO DO WITH ME?

31:09.100 --> 31:11.200
MY NUMBERS ARE WAY DOWN.

31:11.200 --> 31:12.567
I'M REHABILITATING
A BUSTED KNEE,

31:12.567 --> 31:13.867
AND IF I GET TRADED
RIGHT NOW,

31:13.867 --> 31:15.467
I MIGHT AS WELL KISS
MY CAREER GOOD-BYE.

31:15.467 --> 31:16.633
PLAYERS GET TRADED
ALL THE TIME.

31:16.633 --> 31:18.100
YEAH, BUT THE ONLY REASON
WASHINGTON WOULD TAKE ME

31:18.100 --> 31:19.800
IS BECAUSE MY CONTRACT'S UP
NEXT YEAR,

31:19.800 --> 31:21.167
AND WHEN THEY
DON'T RENEW IT,

31:21.167 --> 31:22.700
THEY'LL HAVE $8 MILLION
TO DANGLE

31:22.700 --> 31:24.400
IN FRONT OF SOMEBODY
THEY REALLY WANT.

31:24.400 --> 31:26.100
OKAY, QUINN, STOP. STOP.

31:26.100 --> 31:28.600
OUR LIVES ARE NO LONGER
CONNECTED.

31:28.600 --> 31:30.733
WHY ARE YOU TELLING ME
THIS?

31:30.733 --> 31:32.367
I NEED YOU TO TALK
TO JERRY

31:32.367 --> 31:33.767
AND GET HIM TO KEEP ME HERE

31:33.767 --> 31:34.967
AND GIVE ME SOME MORE TIME
TO PULL MY GAME TOGETHER.

31:34.967 --> 31:37.200
HE MIGHT LISTEN TO YOU.

31:37.200 --> 31:40.267
SO YOU DON'T LIKE
THAT I'M DATING JERRY.

31:40.267 --> 31:42.133
BUT AS LONG AS YOU CAN
USE IT TO YOUR ADVANTAGE,

31:42.133 --> 31:44.300
THEN IT'S OKAY?

31:44.300 --> 31:48.267
QUINN, YOU REACH A NEW LOW
EVERY TIME I TALK TO YOU.

31:48.267 --> 31:51.200
WAIT, WAIT.
VAL, DO THIS FOR ME.

31:51.200 --> 31:52.533
PLEASE.
YOU'RE DESPERATE,

31:52.533 --> 31:54.533
AND IT'S NOT A GOOD LOOK.

31:54.533 --> 31:57.567
FIRST OF ALL, JERRY AND I
DO NOT DISCUSS BUSINESS,

31:57.567 --> 32:01.067
AND EVEN IF WE DID,
YOU WOULD BE THE LAST THING

32:01.067 --> 32:03.533
EITHER ONE OF US
WANTED TO TALK ABOUT.

32:03.533 --> 32:05.067
DON'T YOU THINK
I KNOW THAT?

32:05.067 --> 32:07.500
YOU'VE MADE IT CLEAR HOW YOU
FEEL ABOUT ME. I GET IT.

32:07.500 --> 32:11.633
QUINN, LET'S GO, MAN!
WE ALREADY BEHIND SCHEDULE!

32:11.633 --> 32:13.633
[ HUFFS ]

32:13.633 --> 32:16.100
VALERIE...

32:16.100 --> 32:18.933
IF YOU EVER LOVED ME...

32:18.933 --> 32:20.767
AND I KNOW YOU DID,

32:20.767 --> 32:23.967
YOU'D HAVE A HEART
AND DO THIS.

32:38.967 --> 32:40.367
THERE YOU ARE.

32:40.367 --> 32:41.700
HI.

32:41.700 --> 32:42.767
HEY, DARLING.

32:42.767 --> 32:44.133
[ KISS ]

32:44.133 --> 32:46.267
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE LOST.

32:46.267 --> 32:47.767
OH, NO.

32:47.767 --> 32:49.833
I JUST GOT A LITTLE
TURNED AROUND.

32:49.833 --> 32:51.333
COME ON.

33:00.100 --> 33:02.900
[ MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY ]

33:05.100 --> 33:06.900
[ THUD ]
Man: WHOO!

33:06.900 --> 33:09.533
[ MEN CHEER ]

33:11.233 --> 33:12.633
THANKS FOR COMING.

33:12.633 --> 33:13.833
I HATE THE FACT

33:13.833 --> 33:15.833
THAT I MISSED, UH,
KEISHA'S BRUNCH.

33:15.833 --> 33:17.733
I'M GLAD YOU DIDN'T MAKE IT.
YOU MISSED THE DRAMA.

33:17.733 --> 33:19.167
OH?

33:19.167 --> 33:21.567
IS THAT WHAT'S
BOTHERING YOU?

33:21.567 --> 33:23.733
HUH?
WELL, I CAN TELL YOU GOT
SOMETHING ON YOUR MIND.

33:23.733 --> 33:24.933
IS IT THE FOOD? 'CAUSE...

33:24.933 --> 33:28.067
I CAN GET THEM TO BRING YOU
SOMETHING ELSE.

33:28.067 --> 33:32.267
NO. [ SIGHS ]
THE FOOD IS FINE.

33:32.267 --> 33:34.500
I JUST HAVE SOMETHING
TO TELL YOU.

33:34.500 --> 33:37.067
[ SILVERWARE CLANKS ]

33:37.067 --> 33:38.067
OKAY.

33:38.067 --> 33:39.400
I HAD COFFEE WITH QUINN
THE OTHER DAY.

33:39.400 --> 33:40.533
HE WANTED TO TALK.

33:40.533 --> 33:42.267
LET ME GUESS.

33:42.267 --> 33:47.067
HE'S MISSING YOU,
AND HE WANTS YOU BACK.

33:47.067 --> 33:48.667
NO. [ CHUCKLES ]
NOTHING LIKE THAT.

33:48.667 --> 33:50.133
THEN I SEE HE'S STILL
AN IDIOT

33:50.133 --> 33:52.467
WHEN IT COMES TO YOU.

33:52.467 --> 33:55.733
BUT THEN AGAIN, WE DIDN'T
HIRE HIM FOR HIS BRAINS.

